 I don't agree with it, to a certain degree I think affirmative action is a necessary evil.  It forces those so blinded by their bigotry to hire others and hopefully realize that a person's job performance has no relation to anything except their ability. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udirrabey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dirra Bey</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chanter's Pet</span><br>  Posts: 784<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 4:43:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: So incredibly full of shit I can't even begin...</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, who gave you the power to tell me as a business person that I have to hire someone who is less qualified for the job merely because they were lucky enough to be one of the protected classes?<br>
<br>
And in government -- it makes SO much sense to hire the less qualified to spend our hard earned tax money -- it's just stupid.<br>
<br>
But it does make self-loathing middle class white liberals feel better about themselves.<br>
<br>
A better solution is to provide the opportunities to get people trained and educated and off crack -- so that they will be qualified for the jobs that are now going to them through the luck of the draw.<br>
<br>
