<br>
Even my very own, fortune 500, company has &quot;high&quot; ambitions to hire 20% females by 2010 in to senior management positions. What a joke. 20% is a number some woman &quot;negotiated&quot; with a boardroom of white males to take &quot;baby steps&quot; towards success (and this is a company to employs more then 90,000 people). I am sorry but 20% of 90,000 people aren't &quot;more capable&quot; males. <br>
<br>
To add many multi-national companies financially aid a dictatorial opressive governments which ultimately slaughter their own natives if they speak back on environmental issues or other concerns, all in the name of greed and corporate wealth. To hell with human rights or concern, to hell with civil rights huh? This is &quot;capability&quot; ? The one we are supposed to be hiring the cream of the crop for? Bullshit.<br>
<br>
Before you go making judgements I ask that you go out and study some global companies a bit more deeply, because a random statement about old american quota logic doesn't cut it in the new global world. <br>
<br>
<br>
